# data-models

Core Data Model Hierarchy:

Organization
- Top level entity representing client organizations
- Contains multiple sub-clients for agency relationships
- Associates with gift card pools and campaigns
- Manages user roles and permissions across hierarchy

Campaign
- Links to organization and contacts
- Contains multiple reward conditions
- Tracks delivery methods and fulfillment status 
- Manages personalized URLs and redemption codes

GiftCard
- Belongs to specific brand pools
- Tracks status: available, claimed, delivered, redeemed
- Links to campaigns and redemption conditions
- Contains delivery and redemption audit history

Condition
- Part of campaign reward system
- Defines triggering rules for gift card distribution
- Links to specific gift card pools
- Tracks completion status per recipient

Contact
- Associated with organizations and campaigns
- Contains communication preferences and history
- Tracks engagement across multiple campaigns
- Manages custom field values and segmentation

Key Relationships:
- Organizations can manage multiple client organizations (hierarchical)
- Campaigns belong to single organization but can use multiple gift card pools
- Gift cards are grouped in brand-specific pools with inventory tracking
- Conditions link campaigns to gift card pools with distribution rules
- Contacts can participate in multiple campaigns with separate engagement tracking

Importance Score: 95
- Critical for core business operations
- Enables complex reward distribution workflows
- Supports multi-tenant architecture
- Manages hierarchical client relationships

